The course explains the effects of technological developments on the market and related regulation options.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to explain the market power and welfare in the digital fields (including market definition and assessment of market power). The course also teaches to identify and evaluate the collusion, horizontal agreements and mergers; vertical mergers and restraints; predation, monopolization and other abusive practices in digital fields. It offers the students the policy toolkit based on game theory and imperfect competition models.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student: * Understands the effects of technological developments on market power and the resulting regulation of market failures; * Can see different ways of measuring market power in digital technology areas; * Has an overview of different digital regulation options; * Gets a practical set of tools for shaping the economic content of future regulations.
